line_1: Your tragic Heroes shall not rant,
An English Poet's privilege to rant,
line_2: Sing where you please, in such a cause I grant

line_1: Pride's boundless hope, valour's enthusiast rant,
line_2: With the long nameless train of fancy'd want.

line_1: While Cooss on countless thousands rant,
line_2: How best o' chiels are whyles in want,

line_1: Whence is this vile ungrateful rant?
From antick whim, compos'd of Song and Rant,
line_2: Our hot-brain'd Scribler now will make me cant,
